qas.question: Who can determine a date of adjournment if congress cannot agree?
Who can call congress into emergency session?
Who serves as president of the Senate?
How does Congress exercise a check over the President?
Who has the ability to override any veto made by Congress?
Which veto is the only one Congress is able to override with a two thirds majority?
Who settles the dispute when the President and Vice President cannot come to an agreement for a date of adjournment?
Who serves as President of the Senate and is the only member with voting rights?

context: <a1_0><b4_0>The president<b4_0/><a1_0/> exercises a check over Congress through his <b3_0>power to veto bills<b3_0/>, but Congress may override any veto (excluding the so-called "<b5_0>pocket veto<b5_0/>") by a two-thirds majority in each house. When the <b6_0>two houses of Congress<b6_0/> cannot agree on a date for adjournment, the president may settle the dispute. Either house or both houses may be called into emergency session by the president. <a2_0>The <b7_0>Vice <a0_0>President<b7_0/><a2_0/><a0_0/> serves as president of the Senate, but he may only vote to break a tie.
